org.apache.flume.annotations
Class InterfaceStability

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.flume.annotations.InterfaceStability

@InterfaceAudience.Public
@InterfaceStability.Evolving
public class InterfaceStability
extends Object

Annotation to inform users of how much to rely on a particular package, class or method not changing over time. Currently the stability can be InterfaceStability.Stable, InterfaceStability.Evolving or InterfaceStability.Unstable.

  • All classes that are annotated with Public or LimitedPrivate must have InterfaceStability annotation.
  • Classes that are Private are to be considered unstable unless a different InterfaceStability annotation states otherwise.
  • Incompatible changes must not be made to classes marked as stable.
